    "analysis": "We have followed preprocess → metric anomaly detection → trace analysis. Metric-level severity aggregation highlighted multiple components with severe KPI breaches; cartservice-0 and cartservice-1 are top container-level candidates with extreme severities on CPU throttling KPIs and earliest anomalies at 2022-03-20 19:00:00 UTC+8. Trace analysis shows both cartservice pods have broad, concurrent trace anomalies (many trace KPIs with anomaly_total=60) starting at 19:00:00, primarily on traces from checkoutservice and frontend. Node-level candidates (node-1/2/5/6) show metric severities but no trace anomalies in the window, so they are less likely to be the most downstream root cause. According to the rules, we must now use logs to confirm the resource-level reason (e.g., container CPU throttling, memory, I/O) and to determine whether one specific cartservice pod is the root cause or both. The next step is to inspect logs for cartservice-0 and cartservice-1 (and to confirm whether error_logs contain entries for these pods). This will help confirm the reason (CPU throttling) and the exact occurrence time (first anomalous log or metric point).",
